urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:
If travelling by Coach between Wollongong station and Moss Vale, Exeter or Bundanoon stations you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station.

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.
subtitle: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.

urlText: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked
content: If travelling by Coach to or from Bathurst you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at Bathurst station and your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station. When using Opal you will need to reserve a seat, at no cost, through the Contact Centre by calling 13 22 32 (Between 07:00 to 22:00 each day).
subtitle: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked

urlText: Rozelle bus stop temporary closures
content:
From Sunday 18 August until the end of November 2020 the westbound bus stops on Victoria Rd at Lilyfield Rd (203919) and at Hornsey St (203920) will be closed due to demolition works for the Rozelle Interchange.

The closure is expected to last around 5 months, dependent on weather and maritime conditions.

Please use the existing 507 bus service from Waterview Street to and from the City, or to Meadowbank Station to connect to train services.

In the evenings 507 bus services will be extended to operate between Gladesville and Kissing Point to connect with the M52 bus service operating between the City and Parramatta. Nightly from 9pm to 5am between Wednesday 11 and Friday 27 November, Sydney Metro work will close the bus stop Town Hall Station, Park St, Stand G (2000426) affecting route 311 to Railway Square and 324 and 325 towards Watsons Bay.

The alternative stop will be Town Hall Station, Park St, Stand H (2000429).
subtitle: Park St temporary bus stop changes

urlText: Westmead T-way closure (eastbound only)
content:

The alternative stop will be relocated to Darcy Rd west of Farmhouse Rd.

urlText: Barangaroo Wharf disruptions
content:
From November 6 2020, Barangaroo Wharf 1 and Wharf 2 will be closed at different times while construction works take place.

Regular ferry services will continue without disruption and will use each operational wharf alternatively.

Please follow the signs and staff directions to the operational wharf.
subtitle: Barangaroo Wharf disruptions
